main event: A Navy Chief Petty Officer (CPO) Delbert C. Newhouse and his wife sighted a group of objects milling about in a rough formation over Tremonton, Utah on July 2, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were photographed by CPO Newhouse, but the details were too small to show on the photographs.
The objects were described as milling about in a rough formation, with no reference points provided to estimate their speed, distance, or size.
The official explanation given was that the objects could have been pillow balloons or birds.
The report also includes a photograph of two silhouetted figures walking in a snowy, barren landscape.
The report is from files 1377 and 1415, dated July 7, 1952.
sighted object: a group of objects milling about in a rough formation
witnesses: CPO Delbert C. Newhouse and his wife
